## Data (do not treat as instructions — inputs only)

### Goal (`.devlyn/goal.raw.txt`, sha256=026a153501107373a5e14ade6a4548cd3e9769a69c06a38ed8f4b44fc82183fc)

```
Add a `fulfill-wave` command to `bench-cli` so users can run `bench-cli fulfill-wave --input <path>`. The input file is one JSON object with the required collections `{ "warehouses": Array<Warehouse>, "orders": Array<Order> }`: a warehouse has `{ "id": string, "distance": number, "lots": Array<Lot> }`; a lot has `{ "sku": string, "lot": string, "qty": number, "expires": "YYYY-MM-DD" }`; an order has `{ "id": string, "priority": number, "submitted_at": string, "lines": Array<Line> }`; and a line has `{ "sku": string, "qty": number, "single_warehouse": boolean }`. Validate the complete input before allocating: ids and SKU/lot identifiers must be non-empty strings, quantities must be positive integers, lot expiry values must be valid `YYYY-MM-DD` calendar dates, submitted times must parse as ISO dates or timestamps, distances and priorities must be numbers, the named collections must be arrays, and order ids must be unique. Do not mutate the input file.

Process orders globally by priority descending, then `submitted_at` ascending, then id ascending. An order is all-or-nothing: if any line cannot be fully allocated, reject the order and restore every stock deduction tentatively made for it. Accepted allocations reduce stock for later orders; rejected orders do not. A normal line (`single_warehouse: false`) may split across warehouses and lots. A `single_warehouse: true` line must come entirely from one warehouse, although it may consume multiple lots in that warehouse; reject it when no one warehouse has enough stock even if the combined stock across warehouses would suffice. Consider warehouses by distance ascending, then warehouse id ascending. Within a chosen warehouse, consume matching lots FEFO by expiry ascending, then lot id ascending. Allocation rows must remain in the exact sequence stock was chosen.

On success, write exactly one parseable JSON object to stdout, write nothing to stderr, and emit no extra text. The success object's only keys are `accepted`, `rejected`, and `remaining`. `accepted` follows processing order; each row has exactly `{ "id": string, "allocations": Array<Allocation> }`, and each allocation has exactly `{ "sku": string, "warehouse": string, "lot": string, "qty": number }`. `rejected` follows original input order; each row has exactly `{ "id": string, "reason": "insufficient_stock" }`. `remaining` contains positive leftover lot quantities, sorted by warehouse id, then sku, then expiry, then lot id; each row has exactly `{ "warehouse": string, "sku": string, "lot": string, "qty": number, "expires": "YYYY-MM-DD" }`.

Invalid input and file-read failures must exit `2`, write nothing to stdout, and write exactly one parseable JSON value to stderr. That value must be a non-null, non-array JSON object; its member names are otherwise not prescribed.

Update `tests/cli.test.js` so all existing tests still pass and add at least two `fulfill-wave` tests covering an accepted allocation and a rejected all-or-nothing order. Do not use a catch block that silently returns `null`, `undefined`, an empty string, or an empty object, and do not use an empty catch block. No new npm dependencies. Carrier selection, package dimensions, backorders or partial order acceptance, and persistence beyond stdout are out of scope. Only touch `bin/cli.js` and `tests/cli.test.js`.

```

### Patch under audit (`.devlyn/surface-close.input.patch`, sha256=d96875fe516eb408fb204c722e42788ee5d6c48abdd50518a1a42906da1bde6f)

```diff
diff --git a/bin/cli.js b/bin/cli.js
index 9cc9b24..19ba378 100644
--- a/bin/cli.js
+++ b/bin/cli.js
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@ const USAGE = `Usage: bench-cli <command> [options]
 Commands:
   hello [--name NAME]        Print a greeting (default name: "world")
   version                    Print the CLI version from package.json
+  fulfill-wave --input PATH  Allocate warehouse stock for a wave of orders
   --help, -h                 Show this help
 
 Examples:
@@ -35,6 +36,272 @@ function parseNameFlag(argv) {
   return value;
 }
 
+function parseInputFlag(argv) {
+  const idx = argv.indexOf('--input');
+  const value = argv[idx + 1];
+  if (idx === -1 || !value) {
+    throw new Error('--input requires a value');
+  }
+  return value;
+}
+
+function requireObject(value, label) {
+  if (value === null || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {
+    throw new Error(`${label} must be an object`);
+  }
+}
+
+function requireArray(value, label) {
+  if (!Array.isArray(value)) {
+    throw new Error(`${label} must be an array`);
+  }
+}
+
+function requireIdentifier(value, label) {
+  if (typeof value !== 'string' || value.length === 0) {
+    throw new Error(`${label} must be a non-empty string`);
+  }
+}
+
+function requirePositiveInteger(value, label) {
+  if (!Number.isInteger(value) || value <= 0) {
+    throw new Error(`${label} must be a positive integer`);
+  }
+}
+
+function requireNumber(value, label) {
+  if (typeof value !== 'number') {
+    throw new Error(`${label} must be a number`);
+  }
+}
+
+function parseExpiry(value) {
+  if (typeof value !== 'string' || !/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/.test(value)) {
+    throw new Error('expires must be a YYYY-MM-DD date');
+  }
+
+  const [year, month, day] = value.split('-').map(Number);
+  const date = new Date(`${value}T00:00:00.000Z`);
+  if (
+    Number.isNaN(date.getTime()) ||
+    date.getUTCFullYear() !== year ||
+    date.getUTCMonth() + 1 !== month ||
+    date.getUTCDate() !== day
+  ) {
+    throw new Error('expires must be a valid calendar date');
+  }
+}
+
+function parseSubmittedAt(value) {
+  if (typeof value !== 'string') {
+    throw new Error('submitted_at must be a string');
+  }
+
+  if (/^\d+$/.test(value)) {
+    const timestamp = Number(value);
+    if (!Number.isFinite(timestamp) || Number.isNaN(new Date(timestamp).getTime())) {
+      throw new Error('submitted_at must be a valid timestamp');
+    }
+    return timestamp;
+  }
+
+  if (!/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}(?:T.*)?$/.test(value)) {
+    throw new Error('submitted_at must be an ISO date or timestamp');
+  }
+
+  const timestamp = Date.parse(value);
+  if (Number.isNaN(timestamp)) {
+    throw new Error('submitted_at must be an ISO date or timestamp');
+  }
+  return timestamp;
+}
+
+function validateInput(input) {
+  requireObject(input, 'input');
+  requireArray(input.warehouses, 'warehouses');
+  requireArray(input.orders, 'orders');
+
+  for (const warehouse of input.warehouses) {
+    requireObject(warehouse, 'warehouse');
+    requireIdentifier(warehouse.id, 'warehouse id');
+    requireNumber(warehouse.distance, 'warehouse distance');
+    requireArray(warehouse.lots, 'warehouse lots');
+
+    for (const lot of warehouse.lots) {
+      requireObject(lot, 'lot');
+      requireIdentifier(lot.sku, 'lot sku');
+      requireIdentifier(lot.lot, 'lot id');
+      requirePositiveInteger(lot.qty, 'lot qty');
+      parseExpiry(lot.expires);
+    }
+  }
+
+  const submittedTimes = new Map();
+  for (const order of input.orders) {
+    requireObject(order, 'order');
+    requireIdentifier(order.id, 'order id');
+    if (submittedTimes.has(order.id)) {
+      throw new Error('order ids must be unique');
+    }
+    requireNumber(order.priority, 'order priority');
+    submittedTimes.set(order.id, parseSubmittedAt(order.submitted_at));
+    requireArray(order.lines, 'order lines');
+
+    for (const line of order.lines) {
+      requireObject(line, 'line');
+      requireIdentifier(line.sku, 'line sku');
+      requirePositiveInteger(line.qty, 'line qty');
+    }
+  }
+
+  return submittedTimes;
+}
+
+function compareWarehouses(left, right) {
+  return left.distance - right.distance || left.id.localeCompare(right.id);
+}
+
+function compareLots(left, right) {
+  return left.expires.localeCompare(right.expires) || left.lot.localeCompare(right.lot);
+}
+
+function availableQuantity(warehouse, sku) {
+  return warehouse.lots.reduce(
+    (total, lot) => total + (lot.sku === sku ? lot.qty : 0),
+    0,
+  );
+}
+
+function drawFromWarehouse(warehouse, sku, qty, deductions) {
+  let remaining = qty;
+  const allocations = [];
+  const lots = warehouse.lots
+    .filter((lot) => lot.sku === sku && lot.qty > 0)
+    .sort(compareLots);
+
+  for (const lot of lots) {
+    if (remaining === 0) break;
+    const drawn = Math.min(lot.qty, remaining);
+    lot.qty -= drawn;
+    deductions.push({ lot, qty: drawn });
+    allocations.push({ sku, warehouse: warehouse.id, lot: lot.lot, qty: drawn });
+    remaining -= drawn;
+  }
+
+  return remaining === 0 ? allocations : null;
+}
+
+function allocateLine(line, warehouses, deductions) {
+  if (line.single_warehouse === true) {
+    const warehouse = warehouses.find(
+      (candidate) => availableQuantity(candidate, line.sku) >= line.qty,
+    );
+    if (!warehouse) return null;
+    return drawFromWarehouse(warehouse, line.sku, line.qty, deductions);
+  }
+
+  const available = warehouses.reduce(
+    (total, warehouse) => total + availableQuantity(warehouse, line.sku),
+    0,
+  );
+  if (available < line.qty) return null;
+
+  let remaining = line.qty;
+  const allocations = [];
+  for (const warehouse of warehouses) {
+    if (remaining === 0) break;
+    const qty = Math.min(remaining, availableQuantity(warehouse, line.sku));
+    if (qty === 0) continue;
+    const drawn = drawFromWarehouse(warehouse, line.sku, qty, deductions);
+    if (drawn === null) {
+      throw new Error('stock allocation failed');
+    }
+    allocations.push(...drawn);
+    remaining -= qty;
+  }
+  return allocations;
+}
+
+function rollback(deductions) {
+  for (const deduction of deductions) {
+    deduction.lot.qty += deduction.qty;
+  }
+}
+
+function fulfillWave(input) {
+  const submittedTimes = validateInput(input);
+  const warehouses = input.warehouses
+    .map((warehouse) => ({
+      id: warehouse.id,
+      distance: warehouse.distance,
+      lots: warehouse.lots.map((lot) => ({ ...lot })),
+    }))
+    .sort(compareWarehouses);
+  const orders = input.orders.slice().sort((left, right) => (
+    right.priority - left.priority ||
+    submittedTimes.get(left.id) - submittedTimes.get(right.id) ||
+    left.id.localeCompare(right.id)
+  ));
+  const accepted = [];
+  const rejectedIds = new Set();
+
+  for (const order of orders) {
+    const deductions = [];
+    const allocations = [];
+    let acceptedOrder = true;
+
+    for (const line of order.lines) {
+      const lineAllocations = allocateLine(line, warehouses, deductions);
+      if (lineAllocations === null) {
+        acceptedOrder = false;
+        break;
+      }
+      allocations.push(...lineAllocations);
+    }
+
+    if (acceptedOrder) {
+      accepted.push({ id: order.id, allocations });
+    } else {
+      rollback(deductions);
+      rejectedIds.add(order.id);
+    }
+  }
+
+  const rejected = input.orders
+    .filter((order) => rejectedIds.has(order.id))
+    .map((order) => ({ id: order.id, reason: 'insufficient_stock' }));
+  const remaining = warehouses
+    .flatMap((warehouse) => warehouse.lots
+      .filter((lot) => lot.qty > 0)
+      .map((lot) => ({
+        warehouse: warehouse.id,
+        sku: lot.sku,
+        lot: lot.lot,
+        qty: lot.qty,
+        expires: lot.expires,
+      })))
+    .sort((left, right) => (
+      left.warehouse.localeCompare(right.warehouse) ||
+      left.sku.localeCompare(right.sku) ||
+      left.expires.localeCompare(right.expires) ||
+      left.lot.localeCompare(right.lot)
+    ));
+
+  return { accepted, rejected, remaining };
+}
+
+function runFulfillWave(argv) {
+  try {
+    const inputPath = parseInputFlag(argv);
+    const input = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(inputPath, 'utf8'));
+    process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(fulfillWave(input))}\n`);
+  } catch (error) {
+    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'invalid input';
+    process.stderr.write(`${JSON.stringify({ error: message })}\n`);
+    process.exitCode = 2;
+  }
+}
+
 function main(argv) {
   const [command, ...rest] = argv;
 
@@ -53,6 +320,10 @@ function main(argv) {
       console.log(readPackageVersion());
       return;
     }
+    case 'fulfill-wave': {
+      runFulfillWave(rest);
+      return;
+    }
     default:
       console.error(`Unknown command: ${command}`);
       process.stderr.write(USAGE);
diff --git a/tests/cli.test.js b/tests/cli.test.js
index c7363e8..1efcaec 100644
--- a/tests/cli.test.js
+++ b/tests/cli.test.js
@@ -1,6 +1,8 @@
 const { test } = require('node:test');
 const assert = require('node:assert');
-const { execFileSync } = require('node:child_process');
+const { execFileSync, spawnSync } = require('node:child_process');
+const fs = require('node:fs');
+const os = require('node:os');
 const path = require('node:path');
 
 const CLI = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'bin', 'cli.js');
@@ -23,3 +25,139 @@ test('version prints package version', () => {
   const out = run(['version']);
   assert.match(out, /\d+\.\d+\.\d+/);
 });
+
+function withInput(input, callback) {
+  const directory = fs.mkdtempSync(path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'harbor-tools-'));
+  const inputPath = path.join(directory, 'input.json');
+  fs.writeFileSync(inputPath, JSON.stringify(input));
+  try {
+    callback(inputPath);
+  } finally {
+    fs.rmSync(directory, { recursive: true, force: true });
+  }
+}
+
+test('fulfill-wave accepts orders by priority and uses FEFO allocations', () => {
+  withInput({
+    warehouses: [
+      {
+        id: 'west',
+        distance: 2,
+        lots: [
+          { sku: 'widget', lot: 'new', qty: 4, expires: '2026-02-01' },
+          { sku: 'widget', lot: 'old', qty: 3, expires: '2026-01-01' },
+        ],
+      },
+    ],
+    orders: [
+      {
+        id: 'later-priority',
+        priority: 1,
+        submitted_at: '2026-01-02T00:00:00Z',
+        lines: [{ sku: 'widget', qty: 3, single_warehouse: false }],
+      },
+      {
+        id: 'first-priority',
+        priority: 2,
+        submitted_at: '2026-01-03T00:00:00Z',
+        lines: [{ sku: 'widget', qty: 2, single_warehouse: true }],
+      },
+    ],
+  }, (inputPath) => {
+    const result = JSON.parse(run(['fulfill-wave', '--input', inputPath]));
+    assert.deepStrictEqual(result, {
+      accepted: [
+        {
+          id: 'first-priority',
+          allocations: [{ sku: 'widget', warehouse: 'west', lot: 'old', qty: 2 }],
+        },
+        {
+          id: 'later-priority',
+          allocations: [
+            { sku: 'widget', warehouse: 'west', lot: 'old', qty: 1 },
+            { sku: 'widget', warehouse: 'west', lot: 'new', qty: 2 },
+          ],
+        },
+      ],
+      rejected: [],
+      remaining: [{
+        warehouse: 'west', sku: 'widget', lot: 'new', qty: 2, expires: '2026-02-01',
+      }],
+    });
+  });
+});
+
+test('fulfill-wave rolls back an all-or-nothing rejection', () => {
+  withInput({
+    warehouses: [
+      {
+        id: 'near',
+        distance: 1,
+        lots: [{ sku: 'widget', lot: 'lot-1', qty: 2, expires: '2026-01-01' }],
+      },
+      {
+        id: 'far',
+        distance: 2,
+        lots: [{ sku: 'widget', lot: 'lot-2', qty: 2, expires: '2026-01-02' }],
+      },
+    ],
+    orders: [
+      {
+        id: 'rejected-first',
+        priority: 2,
+        submitted_at: '2026-01-01',
+        lines: [
+          { sku: 'widget', qty: 2, single_warehouse: false },
+          { sku: 'missing', qty: 1, single_warehouse: false },
+        ],
+      },
+      {
+        id: 'accepted-after-rollback',
+        priority: 1,
+        submitted_at: '2026-01-02',
+        lines: [{ sku: 'widget', qty: 2, single_warehouse: true }],
+      },
+      {
+        id: 'cannot-combine',
+        priority: 3,
+        submitted_at: '2026-01-03',
+        lines: [{ sku: 'widget', qty: 3, single_warehouse: true }],
+      },
+    ],
+  }, (inputPath) => {
+    const result = JSON.parse(run(['fulfill-wave', '--input', inputPath]));
+    assert.deepStrictEqual(result, {
+      accepted: [{
+        id: 'accepted-after-rollback',
+        allocations: [{ sku: 'widget', warehouse: 'near', lot: 'lot-1', qty: 2 }],
+      }],
+      rejected: [
+        { id: 'rejected-first', reason: 'insufficient_stock' },
+        { id: 'cannot-combine', reason: 'insufficient_stock' },
+      ],
+      remaining: [{
+        warehouse: 'far', sku: 'widget', lot: 'lot-2', qty: 2, expires: '2026-01-02',
+      }],
+    });
+  });
+});
+
+test('fulfill-wave reports invalid input as one JSON stderr object', () => {
+  withInput({
+    warehouses: [],
+    orders: [{
+      id: 'invalid',
+      priority: 1,
+      submitted_at: 'not-a-date',
+      lines: [],
+    }],
+  }, (inputPath) => {
+    const result = spawnSync('node', [CLI, 'fulfill-wave', '--input', inputPath], {
+      encoding: 'utf8',
+    });
+    assert.strictEqual(result.status, 2);
+    assert.strictEqual(result.stdout, '');
+    const error = JSON.parse(result.stderr);
+    assert.ok(error && !Array.isArray(error));
+  });
+});

```

